      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAST COMMAND (4) won over 1400m here two back then stepped up to the mile and was strong through the line at Doomben last start, beaten just over a length. Rock hard fit and suited back on this bigger track. The one to beat in an even race. MAKE A CALL (5) came from the clouds to score first-up over 1350m then again did his best work late when third over this distance at Doomben last time. Yet to fill a hole in four runs at the Farm which is worrying, but he has never raced better so is worth the benefit of the doubt. NAVAL SEAL (2) won a Class 5 here at this trip two starts ago then found the company last time a bit stiffer. Nicely placed to return to form. REZONE (6) opened this prep with a hat trick before a game second when extended to 1820m here three weeks ago. Must be a chance again with just 54.5kgs. FREE CARRY (3) showed pace but dropped right out first-up in open company. Boasts excellent stats at today's trip and is two for four second-up. Can improve sharply.",
